11:21.827 --> 11:22.608
I have this interest.

11:25.072 --> 11:25.573
We're human.

11:27.897 --> 11:37.772
When God Himself becomes man and lives among us as human, we get to see what we should be like.

11:39.134 --> 11:44.242
We get to see God Himself, the Creator, live as a creature, a holy life.

11:45.538 --> 11:49.222
from which we would learn and have modeled for us the kind of lives we should live.

11:50.122 --> 11:54.226
And Jesus, as God incarnate, is not only human.

11:56.429 --> 12:02.154
And so we see in Him not only example, but divine mercy.

12:03.596 --> 12:04.977
We'll come back to that at the end.

12:05.397 --> 12:14.386
When we watch the life of Christ, when we read the Gospels, again and again, Jesus is giving us example to imitate and

12:14.690 --> 12:19.776
He is doing for us, especially at the cross, what we cannot do for ourselves.

12:20.096 --> 12:21.798
And so he is inimitable.

12:23.039 --> 12:32.470
This is a challenge as you read the gospels, not all imitation, some imitation, some inimitable, you worship.

12:34.012 --> 12:42.962
So let's walk with Jesus here in sequence through his earthly life as this great plan unfolds in history.

12:44.386 --> 12:47.370
Got three steps to move through here this morning.

12:47.430 --> 12:56.143
Number one, Jesus's life work and his lead prayer were his father's glory.

12:57.545 --> 13:04.055
His life work and his lead prayer were his father's glory.

13:05.417 --> 13:11.986
Jesus lived his human life in utter dedication to his father and his father's glory.

13:13.538 --> 13:19.565
When he was born, the angels rightly said, glory to God in the highest.

13:22.048 --> 13:30.058
And in Jesus' earthly life, from the manger to the cross, the man Jesus Christ did not glorify himself.

13:32.241 --> 13:42.994
But in his words and in his deeds, the effect of his life and the expressed intention of his life was to glorify his father.

13:45.282 --> 13:51.111
He summarizes it so briefly and amazingly in John 849.

